And just like that…7 continents done and dusted! 

Just a few days ago I returned from a trip of a lifetime to Antarctica together with @swanhelleniccruises 

It was my 7th and last continent to visit and boy….those rumors are true! It’s such a wild, impressive, magical and most importantly pristine place to visit. 

Travel has always been my passion and turning it into my full time job, creating memories like these and sharing the experiences with others is something I truly enjoy! 

Antarctica still has many secrets for me and I hope to return in the near future, but for now I’m still on cloud nine, trying to process everything I laid my eyes on!

#antarctica #seewhatothersdont #swanhellenic #bucketlist #snow #7thcontinent #expedition #expeditioncruise #shvega

The contrast between the comfort and luxury of the SH Vega and the wild Antarctic coastline couldn’t be more obvious. 

It might only been a little over 2 weeks since we left the white continent, but this throwback Thursday there’s little else I can think about. 

#antarctica #expedition #cruise @swanhelleniccruises #seewhatothersdont #poolgoals #contrast #wildnature

Just your everyday zodiac cruise in Antarctica where penguins jump out of the water everywhere you look, the ice bergs float by and the sense of tranquility is overpowering!

#Antarctica #zodiac #cruise #swanhellenic #expedition #seewhatothersdont

#sunset #Antarctica #landscapephotography #golden #mountains @swanhelleniccruises #seewhatothersdont

A Weddell seal is doing what he does best…..sleeping! Their grey colour and light fur makes them one of the prettiest out there. 

#wildlife #seal #closeup #Antarctica #fur #grey #seewhatothersdont

Slowly sailing through a narrow channel adorned with icebergs, glaciers and mountains while the tranquil waters reflect every little detail. Eerily quiet…ridiculously beautiful…quintessential Antarctica! 

#Antarctica #adventuretravel #expedition #cruise #winterwonderland

#penguins #antarctica #wildlifephotography #animallover #wildlife #expedition #cruise

#ship #swanhellenic #beautiful #engineering #stylish #expedition #travel

#weekend #seal #Antarctica #wildlife #beautifuldestinations #seewhatothersdont

When “taking a stroll” gets a whole new meaning…

#Antarctica #landscape #landscapephotography #iceberg #adventuretravel #winterwonderland

You all know I’m a wildlife enthusiast and it often influences the places I go or visit. Antarctica as a whole was something I wanted to experience and discover, but the fact there’s an abundance of animals to find surely added to the overall excitement to go on a journey to this white desert. 
Planet earth is such a beautiful place, now we only need to find a way to protect it from ourselves! 

#animallover #wildlife #conservation #protection #Antarctica #penguin #wildlifephotography #closeup

Every time you look around in Antarctica there’s another picture perfect frame and moment which is so hard to capture cause the images never do it justice. 
But not only that….there’s also plenty of wildlife that constantly pops up out of nowhere, be it whales or orcas coming up for a fresh breath of air or some penguins or seals resting on an iceberg, there is literally always something to see. 

This image is the perfect example….while watching the golden glow on the clouds thanks to the sun standing very low on the horizon at 11pm there were a few orcas that passed by. It’s all so serene and surreal, but at the same time incredibly beautiful. 

I said it before and will say it again, Antarctica is a place that leaves you speechless and where you realize we’re just a small dot on this blue planet. 

#antarctica #orca #sunset #mountains #capturethemoment #bliss

Killer whales….they are smart, fast and glide through the water like bullets.

We were very fortunate to have a pod of orcas passing by our ship and they were kind enough to let us take a few snapshots of them, the youngsters included!

#orca #killerwhale #antarctica #wildlife #wildlifephotography #whale #travelphotography

Isn’t she a beauty? The @swanhelleniccruises SH Vega is the perfect ship to explore this white desert! Only a maximum of 152 guests and 120 staff to make sure the whole operation runs smoothly! 

State of the art technology, beautiful both on the inside and outside, but most importantly of all able to break ice where it’s needed and guarantee a safe voyage to the polar regions. 

#ship #design #icebreaker #Antarctica #swanhellenic #iceberg #cruise #kreuzfahrt

Weddell seals might look cute and bulky, but once they’re in the water they quickly become a formidable force and that cute face hides the skilled hunter they are. Fish, squid and octopus are all on the menu! 

#wildlifephotography #Antarctica #seal #animallover #wildlifeplanet #wildlife

The contrast between life onboard the @swanhelleniccruises SH Vega and the harsh, cold and rough destinations it travels to couldn’t be bigger. 
It’s truly a joy to experience these beautiful polar regions from the comfort and warmth of a purpose built ship that offers everything you could wish for and then some. 

#cruise #ship #design #interior #comfortzone #safehaven #luxurytravel

The emperor penguin!! By far the most rare sighting we had during our expedition in Antarctica! It was even a first for a few members of the expedition team, so you can imagine how rare these are on the Antarctic peninsula. 

There are still thousands of them left, but they live more inland and in places almost nobody reaches. This is a juvenile but the yellow colour is starting to pop up and soon it will be as majestic as the rest of its family! 

The crew had received intel about this lone emperor penguin being spotted on Tay Head island, a place rarely visited by any expedition. But as the @swanhelleniccruises slogan says “See what others don’t” the expedition team managed to find a landing spot and gave us all the opportunity to see this beauty in its natural habitat. Truly a stunning sighting which we all celebrated afterwards on board the ship!

#penguin #emperor #emperorpenguin #rarebeauty #raresight #seewhatothersdont

As many of you might have seen on my insta-stories last week, I was sailing on one of the most unique ships in the world: Le Commandant Charcot!

@lecommandantcharcot is a luxury icebreaker from @ponant equipped with a hybrid liquefied natural gas propulsion system and some massive high-capacity batteries. It’s the only one of its kind and this ship is capable of reaching the most remote places on this planet like the actual North Pole (yes, the one at 90’degrees), the Ross sea and anything else that seemed impossible before. 

And it’s guests (there are 123 staterooms onboard) can enjoy some of the most luxurious ships currently sailing the seven seas while crossing these inhospitable environments. 

If you haven’t seen any of my onboard content, I’ll make sure to put it all in a highlight which you can check afterwards. 

And while the taste of caviar and champagne is slowly starting to fade, I realize I only scratched the surface of what this amazing ship has to offer and how it feels to sail on Le Commandant Charcot in some of the toughest regions in the world. 

#lecommandantcharcot #ponant #luxurycruise #luxurytravel #expedition #travel

The @lecommandantcharcot is such an advanced exploration vessel, that most of the technology isn’t even noticeable with the naked eye. 

For example all outdoor decks are heated, meaning no snow or ice will hinder you from going out. They use recovered energy to do all that, and that’s just one tiny little detail while there are literally countless examples like this. 

The Blue Lagoon (pictured here) is one of the most stunning outdoor spaces I’ve even seen on a ship. The hot & cold pool that surround the seating area do give you the impression you’re in Iceland enjoying one of the thermal lagoons indeed. 

@ponant really kicked it outside the park with Le Commandant Charcot and it’s truly a naval masterpiece that needs to be experienced to fully grasp the uniqueness of it! 

#Ponant #LeCommandantCharcot #luxurycruise #luxurytravel #cruise #expedition #travel

One of my favorite moments onboard a ship is when you wake up early in the morning and witness the sunrise while knowing all the rest is still asleep (the bridge and staff not included of course).

It might have been the jet lag, or the excitement of being on @lecommandantcharcot , or just the fact that I always want to experience everything and happily sacrifice some sleep to see the sun come up. In the end it doesn’t really matter, the moment has become a great memory and I wouldn’t want it any other way. 

#sunrise #cruiselife #cruise #cruiseship #LeCommandantCharcot #Ponant

I was so happy to be back in London last month. Having some spare time to stroll around the city was a luxury I hadn’t enjoyed for a while. 

Of course I couldn’t ignore the amazing Natural History Museum which is housed in an amazing building and where this blue whale skeleton makes your jaws drop from the moment you walk in. 
I remember visiting this place when I was a teenager and today it still takes my breath away! 

#London #UK #NaturalHistoryMuseum #whale #skeleton #architecture

As most of you know I wasn’t really impressed with my recent flight on @flyswiss which is mainly due to lack of service. 

The crew were great and this throne seat is ideal for solo travelers but only having one meal service on an 8 hour intercontinental day-flight in business class is just not right. 

I still like the brand and Zurich is one, if not the most enjoyable airport to use for intercontinental flights leaving or arriving in mainland Europe, but they really need to rethink their service in order to compete with the competition. 

#swiss #swissair #aviation #avgeek #businessclass #service #unhappy

It’s been a while since I’ve posted but sometimes life just takes over and that’s exactly what happened.

Nonetheless I’ll make sure to catch up on posts and images from my recent trips. 

As mentioned on my stories (which luckily remain in real-time) we asked our son what he liked for his birthday; a party or a small surprise getaway. Being our son he picked the latter and we wouldn’t have wanted it any other way. 

As a result we took him for a midweek to one of his favorite destinations being the Maldives! And our first stop was the beautiful @ooreethirah which has consistently been among the best properties since it opened up over a decade ago. 

Our pool villa was pretty perfect for the kids to enjoy themselves if they weren’t playing somewhere else on the island. 
And to be fair……we were equally happy to lounge in the massive private pool while sipping some bubbly and enjoying the light ocean breeze. 

#maldives #oneandonly #reethirah #privatepool #luxurytravel

When you find that perfect spot to relax and soak it all in….

This is your breakfast view at @gili.lankanfushi and I can’t think of a better way to start your day in paradise.
